value.title: Herschel Walker tells James Clyburn he took Trump out of context with latest criticism
value.excerpt: Former NFL star Herschel Walker pushed back on House Majority Whip James Clyburn, D-S.C., on Sunday after the latter said that President Trump called a Black woman a dog.

value.title: Conway makes case for Trump reelection: 'The antidote to uncertainty is not more uncertainty'
value.excerpt: Reelecting President Trump is in the best interest of the American people, former counselor to the president Kellyanne Conway told Fox News' "Democracy 2020 Election Preview" Sunday.

value.title: Trump says votes should be counted by Election Day at Georgia rally
value.excerpt: Trump said extensions could allow “bad things happen in places like Pennsylvania and Nevada.”

value.title: Biden banks on Hollywood support in final days before 2020 election
value.excerpt: Hillary Clinton employed a similar strategy in 2016, when she won the popular vote but lost the Electoral College.

value.title: Biden's campaign bundlers include Wall Street billionaires, entertainment moguls
value.excerpt: Democratic presidential candidate Joe Biden unveiled a list of his biggest fundraisers Saturday night, revealing a campaign powered in part by Wall Street executives, Silicon Valley billionaires and entertainment moguls.

value.title: Massive lines at Trump rally in battleground state North Carolina
value.excerpt: Supporters reportedly lined up hours in advance for President Trump's rally in Hickory, North Carolina on Sunday.

value.title: Lady Gaga and John Legend to join Joe Biden and Kamala Harris for final campaign events
value.excerpt: Superstars Lady Gaga and John Legend will join Joe Biden and Kamala Harris for their final respective events on the campaign trail on the eve of Election Day, the Biden campaign announced Sunday.

value.title: Joe Biden becomes 'an underdog' if he doesn't win Pa., says Nate Silver
value.excerpt: Without Pennsylvania and its 20 electoral votes, Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden will become “an underdog,” the founder of an opinion poll analysis website, FiveThirtyEight, said on Sunday.

value.title: Trump campaign hits back at Buttigieg's claim that Trump 'took credit' for Obama economy
value.excerpt: Mayor Pete Buttigieg was wrong about 2020 Democratic presidential hopeful Joe Biden's economic agenda being better for Americans, said Trump 2020 Communications Director Tim Murtaugh on Sunday, two days away from Election Day.

value.title: Joe Biden is ‘last shot’ for establishment Democrats, says Lawrence Jones
value.excerpt: Progressivism will gain momentum in the Democratic Party if Joe Biden loses the election, Fox Nation host Lawrence Jones said on Sunday.

value.title: Hunter Biden's business was 'industrial-scale' corruption: Graham
value.excerpt: Senate Judiciary Committee Chairman Lindsey Graham, R-S.C., said Sunday that he plans on holding a hearing where he will ask the FBI why they sat on the laptop believed to have belonged to Hunter Biden for almost a year without taking action.

value.title: Gov. Huckabee believes President Trump will get reelected by a 'substantial' margin
value.excerpt: Former Arkansas Gov. Mike Huckabee believes President Trump will win the 2020 election by a “substantial” margin, telling “Fox & Friends” on Sunday that “it will cause people's heads to explode because they just can’t see it coming.”

value.title: Trump, Ernst take leads over Dem challengers in Iowa poll
value.excerpt: Just days before Election Day, both President Trump and U.S. Sen. Joni Ernst have pulled ahead of their Democratic challengers in the assessment of Iowa voters, a new poll shows.

value.title: Ivanka Trump breaks Obama record on way to $35M-plus fundraising haul: reports
value.excerpt: Ivanka Trump, White House senior adviser and first daughter, has reportedly raised tens of millions of dollars for her father’s reelection and even broke former President Obama’s single-day fundraising record at a Texas stop in September.

value.title: 'Shoot your shot': Obama nails three-pointer while campaigning with Biden in Michigan
value.excerpt: Barack Obama called game.

value.title: Trump announces day of remembrance for Americans killed by illegal immigrants
value.excerpt: President Trump on Friday declared Nov. 1 a day of remembrance for Americans killed by illegal immigrants -- seeking to highlight his policies curbing illegal immigration in the last days of his reelection campaign.

value.title: California pastor explains Trump vote with 'clear conscience'
value.excerpt: California pastor Bill Johnson of Bethel Church explains why he is voting for President Trump with 'confidence' after comparing his record to Joe Biden's.

value.title: Obama, Biden to make first joint appearance in Michigan
value.excerpt: Democrats are bringing their firepower to Michigan, the critical swing state that helped seal President Trump's 2016 victory.

value.title: Kayleigh McEnany says SEALs' rescue of American hostage is 'story of' Trump presidency: 'We don't stop'
value.excerpt: The American hostage rescued in West Africa by SEAL Team 6 in a daring raid is part of President Trump's exceptional accomplishments, Kayleigh McEnany said Saturday.

value.title: Ivanka Trump says she is 'unapologetically' pro-life
value.excerpt: Ivanka Trump this week said that she is “unapologetically” pro-life, adding that motherhood changed how she thinks about the abortion issue.

value.title: Top two pro-Trump super PACs make final $20 million ad push
value.excerpt: The two leading super PACs that are supporting President Trump's re-election bid are teaming up to shell out $20 million to run ads on TV and digital in seven crucial general election battleground in the closing stretch leading up to Election Day on Tuesday.

value.title: Facebook manually limited New York Post Hunter Biden story: Report
value.excerpt: Facebook fact-checkers manually flagged and restricted distribution of the New York Post's Hunter Biden story, documents obtained by The Guardian show.

value.title: Scott Walker claims Trump has 'fighting chance' in Wisconsin, touts Favre endorsement of president
value.excerpt: President Trump has a "fighting chance" to pull off a surprise victory in Wisconsin, repeating his feat of four years ago, former Republican Gov. Scott Walker told "Your World" Friday.

value.title: Pence returns to Arizona for final push to flip liberal-leaning cities
value.excerpt: In an effort to pick up voters from more progressive counties that voted against the president in 2016, Vice President Mike Pence is returning to the key battleground state of Arizona on Friday.

value.title: NFL legend Brett Favre endorses Trump for president
value.excerpt: NFL great Brett Favre has endorsed President Donald Trump for reelection. He's one of the most prominent figures in sports to publicly pledge support for the President.
